<P>The&s;e Arguments in our World would
have been unan&s;werable, but when they
came to be brought to <HI>the Te&s;t of Lunar
Rea&s;oning,</HI> alas they &s;ignify'd nothing;
they <HI>di&s;tingui&s;ht</HI> and <HI>di&s;tingui&s;ht</HI> till they
brought the <HI>Pre&s;tarian War</HI> to be meer
Rebellion, <HI>King-killing,</HI> Bloody and <HI>&V;n|natural;</HI>
and the <HI>Solunarian</HI> fighting a|gain&s;t
their King, and <HI>turning him adrift</HI>
to &s;eek his Fortune, <HI>no prejudice at all to
